n2-ng (0.1.2-1) kali-rolling; urgency=medium

  * Fix 100% CPU / GUI freeze when starting monitor mode: airodump-ng's
    continuous ANSI screen redraws flooded the Raw View, whose per-line
    widget updates starved the Tk event loop. Raw View updates are now
    batched (single layout pass per refresh, capped at MAX_LINES) and the
    worker's raw-line buffer is bounded.
  * Add a re-entrancy guard to the display refresh loop and enforce
    single self-rescheduling after() chains (capture size monitor, capture
    poll, signal graph retry), with all timers cancelled on window close.
  * Route hashcat and attack output to the UI via queue + after() pump
    instead of touching Tk widgets from worker threads.

 -- KiMiGuEL — INDEPENTEST <Indepentest@gmail.com>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 22:37:00 -0700

